  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nComponent: forge test\r\n\r\nSo I've been testing my contracts and can't find a way to store a signature generated by a wallet to bytes memory.\r\nDuring this time I also found a way to bypass this on the `.t.sol` by using `vm.setEnv`  and retrieve the value using `vm.envBytes`\r\n\r\nNow my problem is I am using a fuzzer on my test and this `got val:` log is taking all the space on the terminal exceeding it's default limit that using the search feature of the terminal won't even register them since they've been truncated.\r\n\r\nNow, I've tried `--silence` which did nothing.\r\n\r\nThis is making it hard for me to view other test's result / console2.log since they've already been truncated.\r\n\r\nso is there a way for us to have a flag or config of some sort that would silence `vm.env` output logs? \n\n### Additional context\n\nThis is an example of the `got val:` logs I am talking about\r\n![image](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/assets/110418886/9f05a327-ba5b-49ff-9167-9e37b0b83954)\r\n",
